@Node "M531" "ImageDeskE.guide/M531"
@Next "M532"
@Toc "M53"

Project
-------


 @{" New              A N " Link "M5311"}      
 @{" Open             A O " Link "M5312"}      
 @{" Close            A C " Link "M5313"}      
 @{" Save as...       A S " Link "M5314"}      
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 @{" Generate Catalog A G " Link "M5315"}      
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 @{" Execute Arexx    A X " Link "M5316"}      
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 @{" Information      A I " Link "M5317"}      
 @{" About...             " Link "M5318"}      
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 @{" Quit             A Q " Link "M5319"} 


@EndNode

@Node "M5311" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5311"
@Next "M5312"
@Toc "M531"

New
...

First of all a requester asks for path and  pattern  of  files  to  be
processed. If this requester is confirmed positively, ImageDesk closes
the current catalog  buffer  and  opens  a  new  one.  After  that  it
generates  a  thumbnail  object for all selected and supported images,
adds it to the new buffer and lets it appear on the desk.


@EndNode

@Node "M5312" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5312"
@Next "M5313"
@Prev "M5311"
@Toc "M531"

Open
....

An ImageDesk catalog file will be loaded into a new catalog buffer  if
the  selected  file  is  identified  as  a correct catalog. A formerly
opened catalog buffer will be closed before the new one is opened.


@EndNode

@Node "M5313" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5313"
@Next "M5314"
@Prev "M5312"
@Toc "M531"

Close
.....

If there is an active  catalog  buffer  it  will  be  closed  after  a
optional  confirmation  request.  Its  allocated system memory will be
freed.


@EndNode

@Node "M5314" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5314"
@Next "M5315"
@Prev "M5313"
@Toc "M531"

Save as...
..........

Saves the current catalog buffer into one single  file.  You  will  be
prompted  for  a  file  name  by a requester. It takes care of the @{i}XPK
Prefs@{ui}, but ignores the value in @{i}max. entries per catalog@{ui}.


@EndNode

@Node "M5315" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5315"
@Next "M5316"
@Prev "M5314"
@Toc "M531"

Generate Catalog
................

This menu item branches into two subitems:

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}Show Thumbnails@{ub} - First a file name is requested for the
     catalog file to be generated. After this another requester opens
     where path and pattern for the picture files can be choosen. Any
     additionally selected files will be ignored. If the @{b}OK@{ub}-button has
     been pressed, ImageDesk starts to examine all of the files listed
     in the requester for being in a supported format. In each case in
     which they are a supported format, a thumbnail object will be
     generated which appears as an intuition gadget on the screen and
     which will be added to the catalog buffer.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}Hidden@{ub} - Acts exactly like @{b}Show Thumbnails@{ub}, but the generated
     thumbnail images won't appear on the desk.

The process monitor which appears during the generation process helps by
estimating the current state of the procedure. To stop the thumbnail
generation, press the ESC-key and it will be interrupted on the next
possible point of time. @{b}Generate Catalog@{ub} takes care of the @{i}XPK Prefs@{ui}
and @{i}max. entries per catalog@{ui} in @{i}System Prefs@{ui}.

@{i}Remark:@{ui} If the generation process has  been  interrupted,  all  former
generated objects will be saved correctly.


@EndNode

@Node "M5316" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5316"
@Next "M5317"
@Prev "M5315"
@Toc "M531"

Execute Arexx
.............

Executes an Arexx script which has to be selected by a file requester


@EndNode

@Node "M5317" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5317"
@Next "M5318"
@Prev "M5316"
@Toc "M531"

Information
...........

Opens a information window which tells:

   @{b}*@{ub} Name of the public screen

   @{b}*@{ub} Name of the AREXX port

   @{b}*@{ub} Graphics board mode

   @{b}*@{ub} Currently valid thumbnail sizes

   @{b}*@{ub} Available memory

   @{b}*@{ub} Thumbnail deskspace

   @{b}*@{ub} Number of thumbnail objects used


@EndNode

@Node "M5318" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5318"
@Next "M5319"
@Prev "M5317"
@Toc "M531"

About
.....

Opens a information window which tells about program  version,  author
and whether you are a registered user.


@EndNode

@Node "M5319" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5319"
@Prev "M5318"
@Toc "M531"

Quit
....

Exits ImageDesk after a confirmation request. The  current  preference
settings can be saved before you exit.


@EndNode

@Node "M532" "ImageDeskE.guide/M532"
@Next "M533"
@Prev "M531"
@Toc "M53"

Edit Buffer
-----------


 @{" Add Thumbnail       A H " Link "M5321"}      
 @{" Add Multiple        A U " Link "M5322"}      
 @{" Remove Entries...   A E " Link "M5323"}      
 @{" Change Picture Path A & " Link "M5324"}      
