@Node "M5321" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5321"
@Next "M5322"
@Toc "M532"

Add Thumbnail
.............

Adds a thumbnail object to the catalog buffer which has to be selected
in  a  file  requester. The path for the images is given and cannot be
changed.


@EndNode

@Node "M5322" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5322"
@Next "M5323"
@Prev "M5321"
@Toc "M532"

Add Multiple
............

Several picture files can be choosen by specifying a search pattern in
the  file  requester.  The  path for the images is given and cannot be
changed.


@EndNode

@Node "M5323" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5323"
@Next "M5324"
@Prev "M5322"
@Toc "M532"

Remove Entries...
.................

Opens a window which lists all entries of the catalog buffer and shows
the  selected  thumbnail.  Every  listed entry can be removed from the
buffer.


@EndNode

@Node "M5324" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5324"
@Next "M5325"
@Prev "M5323"
@Toc "M532"

Change Picture Path
...................

If the path of cataloged pictures has changed, it has to be changed in
the catalog, too. Former it was necessary to use @{b}CATChPath@{ub} for this
job. Now ImageDesk can do it internally.

If this menu item has been selected, a requester appears in which you
have to choose the new path. After the selection, ImageDesk changes the
picture path of the current catalog buffer to your selection.  All
visible thumbnail-objects will be redrawn afterwards to apply this
patch change to them, too. unbuffered thumbnails will be lost.


@EndNode

@Node "M5325" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5325"
@Prev "M5324"
@Toc "M532"

Update
......


 @{" Completely            A K " Link "M53251"}       
 @{" Only Add New          A F " Link "M53252"}       
 @{" Only Remove Exceeded  A J " Link "M53253"} 


@EndNode

@Node "M53251" "ImageDeskE.guide/M53251"
@Next "M53252"
@Toc "M5325"

Completely
..........

Tries automatically to do a complete update of the catalog buffer.  It
will  be  testet  if  there  are  uncataloged  images  in  the picture
directory and then generates thumbnail objects for them. Besides this,
every catalog entry will be checked if its corresponding picture still
exists. If not the thumbnail will be removed.


@EndNode

@Node "M53252" "ImageDeskE.guide/M53252"
@Next "M53253"
@Prev "M53251"
@Toc "M5325"

Only Add New
............

Tries to find all uncataloged files of the picture  directory  and  to
generate thumbnail objects for them which will be added to the catalog
buffer.


@EndNode

@Node "M53253" "ImageDeskE.guide/M53253"
@Prev "M53252"
@Toc "M5325"

Only Remove Exceeded
....................

Removes thumbnail objects from the catalog buffer which corresponding
pictures does not exist anymore.


@EndNode

@Node "M533" "ImageDeskE.guide/M533"
@Next "M534"
@Prev "M532"
@Toc "M53"

Edit Page
---------

The menu items contained here serve for adding or  removing  thumbnail
objects  from  the  desk.  It will @{i}not@{ui} have any effects on the catalog
buffer.


 @{" Redraw           A W " Link "M5330"}      
 @{" Add Thumbnail    A A " Link "M5331"}      
 @{" Remove Thumbnail A R " Link "M5332"}      
 @{" Clean Whole Desk A D " Link "M5333"}      
 @{" Mark & Delete    A M " Link "M5334"} 


@EndNode

@Node "M5330" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5330"
@Next "M5331"
@Toc "M533"

Redraw
......

The current Page will be fully redrawn. All unbuffered thumbnails will
be lost.


@EndNode

@Node "M5331" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5331"
@Next "M5332"
@Prev "M5330"
@Toc "M533"

Add Thumbnail
.............

A file name for a picture is requested and a thumbnail object will  be
generated for it on the desk.


@EndNode

@Node "M5332" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5332"
@Next "M5333"
@Prev "M5331"
@Toc "M533"

Remove Thumbnail
................

The thumbnail object selected next will be removed from the desk.


@EndNode

@Node "M5333" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5333"
@Next "M5334"
@Prev "M5332"
@Toc "M533"

Clean Whole Desk
................

All thumbnail objects will be removed form the desk. Depending on  the
current   preferences  a  confirmation  request  is  made  before  the
operation is performed.


@EndNode

@Node "M5334" "ImageDeskE.guide/M5334"
@Prev "M5333"
@Toc "M533"

Mark & Delete
.............

First of all, ImageDesk  turns  into  a  marking  mode.  You  will  be
prompted  to mark all thumbnail objects you want to remove by clicking
them with the mouse. ImageDesk confirms  this  by  rendering  a  frame
around  the  object.  At  this  point  of time it is still possible to
unmark selected  objects  by  clicking  them  again.  If  the  marking
procedure  is  finished this menu item @{i}has to be@{ui} choosen again and all
marked objects will be removed.


@EndNode

