VIEWIMAGE
---------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}VIEWIMAGE [<FileName>]@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} If <FileName> is given the  corresponding  image  will  be
displayed.  Otherwise you will be prompted for an image file by a file
requester.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}VIEWIMAGE@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63A" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63A"
@Next "M63B"
@Prev "M639"
@Toc "M63"

VIEWPATH
--------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}VIEWPATH [<Path> [<Pattern>]]@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} If <Path> and <Pattern> were given all known image files
which  match the  pattern  will  be  displayed.  If <Pattern> was not
specified the default pattern "#?" will be used. Without any argument
you  will  be prompted for path and pattern by a requester.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}VIEWPATH "work:pics/gif" "#?.gif"@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63B" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63B"
@Next "M63C"
@Prev "M63A"
@Toc "M63"

LOADPREFS
---------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}LOADPREFS [<FileName>]@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Tries to read the configuration  file  <FileName>.  If
<FileName>  is missing you will be prompted for one by a file requester.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}LOADPREFS "ImageDesk.idprefs"@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63C" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63C"
@Next "M63D"
@Prev "M63B"
@Toc "M63"

SAVEPREFS
---------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}SAVEPREFS [<FileName>]@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Tries to save the current configuration under the name
<FileName>  if specified. Otherwise you will be requested for a file
name.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}SAVEPREFS@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63D" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63D"
@Next "M63E"
@Prev "M63C"
@Toc "M63"

MAKETHUMBNAIL
-------------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}MAKETHUMBNAIL [<FileName>]@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Generates a single thumbnail object from the image file
<FileName>. If <FileName> is missing you have to select one in a file
requester.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}MAKETHUMBNAIL@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63E" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63E"
@Next "M63F"
@Prev "M63D"
@Toc "M63"

GENTHUMBNAILS
-------------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}GENTHUMBNAILS [<Path> [<Pattern>]]@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} If <Path> and <Pattern> were given for all  known  image
files  which match  the  pattern a thumbnail object will be generated.
If <Pattern> was not specified the default pattern "#?" will be used.
Without  any argument you will be prompted for path and pattern by a
requester.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}GENTHUMBNAILS "work:pics/gif" "#?.gif"@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63F" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63F"
@Next "M63G"
@Prev "M63E"
@Toc "M63"

DESKTOFRONT
-----------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}DESKTOFRONT@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Switches ImageDesk's screen into front.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}DESKTOFRONT@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63G" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63G"
@Next "M63H"
@Prev "M63F"
@Toc "M63"

DESKTOBACK
----------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}DESKTOBACK@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Switches ImageDesk's screen to back.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}DESKTOBACK@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63H" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63H"
@Next "M63I"
@Prev "M63G"
@Toc "M63"

OPENCAT
-------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}OPENCAT [<FileName> [<startindex> <num>]]@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} If a file name was given ImageDesk tries to open a
thumbnail  catalog file.  Otherwise  you  will  be  prompted for a file
name. If you also specify <startindex> and <num> besides <FileName>
only  the  selected range  will  be  displayed on the screen (although
the catalog will be loaded completely into the buffer).

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}OPENCAT "work:catalogs/gifpics.cat"@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63I" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63I"
@Next "M63J"
@Prev "M63H"
@Toc "M63"

GENCAT
------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}GENCAT [<FileName> [<Path> [<Pattern>]]]@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Generates a thumbnail catalog file with the name
<FileName>  for  all known images in <Path> which match the pattern
<Pattern>. If <Pattern> was not specified the default pattern "#?" will
be used. If GENCAT  is called  with  <FileName>  only,  ImageDesk  asks
for path and pattern.  Without any argument you will additionally be
asked for a file name.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}GENCAT "work:catalogs/gifpics.cat" "work:pics/gif" "#?.gif"@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63J" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63J"
@Next "M63K"
@Prev "M63I"
@Toc "M63"

QUIETGENCAT
-----------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}QUIETGENCAT [<FileName> [<Path> [<Pattern>]]]@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Same behavior as GENCAT but QUIETGENCAT will not display
the generated thumbnail images on the desk.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}QUIETGENCAT "work:cat/gifpics.cat" "work:pics/gif" "#?.gif"@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63K" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63K"
@Next "M63L"
@Prev "M63J"
@Toc "M63"

IDGETFILE
---------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}IDGETFILE <Title>@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Opens a file requester with the title text <Title>.

@{i}Result:@{ui} Choosen file name or NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}IDGETFILE '"Please choose a file"'@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63L" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63L"
@Next "M63M"
@Prev "M63K"
@Toc "M63"

IDGETPATH
---------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}IDGETPATH <Title>@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Opens a path requester with the title text <Title>.

@{i}Result:@{ui} Choosen path or NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}IDGETPATH '"Please Choose a path"'@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63M" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63M"
@Next "M63N"
@Prev "M63L"
@Toc "M63"

GETSPREFS
---------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}GETSPREFS <KeyWord>@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Supplies the value of a single system  prefs  adjustment.
The  result type depends on <KeyWord>. Valid keywords are:

   - PROJECTICONS (-> System Prefs "Save Project Icons")

   - PRINTCOMMAND (-> System Prefs "Print Execution Command")

   - USEDTYPES    (-> System Prefs "Use Datatypes")

   - USEXPK       (-> System Prefs "Use Xpk for Catalogs")

   - XPKPACKER    (-> System Prefs "Xpk")

   - XPKPASSWD    (-> System Prefs "Password")

   - XPKEFFIC     (-> System Prefs "Xpk Efficiency")

   - OUTWIN       (-> System Prefs "Output Window")

   - MAXENTRIES   (-> System Prefs "Max Entries per catalog")

   - DEFAREXX     (-> System Prefs "Default AREXX Script")

   - DEFACTION    (-> System Prefs "Default Action")

   - CONFIRM      (-> Menu item "Confirmation Requests")

   - STATUSBAR    (-> Menu item "Hide Statusbar")

   - SHOWTITLE    (-> Menu item "Hide Title")

@{i}Result:@{ui} Depends on the keyword

   - PROJECTICONS (BOOLEAN)

   - PRINTCOMMAND (BOOLEAN)

   - USEDTYPES    (BOOLEAN)

   - USEXPK       (BOOLEAN)

   - XPKPACKER    (STRING)

   - XPKPASSWD    (STRING)

   - XPKEFFIC     (INTEGER)

   - OUTWIN       (STRING)

   - MAXENTRIES   (STRING)

   - DEFAREXX     (STRING)

   - DEFACTION    ("REQ", "VIW" or "REX")

   - CONFIRM      (BOOLEAN)

   - STATUSBAR    (BOOLEAN)

   - SHOWTITLE    (BOOLEAN)

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}GETSPREFS MAXENTRIES@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63N" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63N"
@Next "M63O"
@Prev "M63M"
@Toc "M63"

SETSPREFS
---------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}SETSPREFS <KeyWord> <Value>@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Sets a single system prefs adjustment to <Value> (see also
GETSPREFS).  The  argument type of <Value> depends on the argument
<KeyWord>. Valid keywords are:

   - PROJECTICONS (BOOLEAN)

   - PRINTCOMMAND (BOOLEAN)

   - USEDTYPES    (BOOLEAN)

   - USEXPK       (BOOLEAN)

   - XPKPACKER    (STRING)

   - XPKPASSWD    (STRING)

   - XPKEFFIC     (INTEGER)

   - OUTWIN       (STRING)

   - MAXENTRIES   (STRING)

   - DEFAREXX     (STRING)

   - DEFACTION    ("REQ", "VIW" or "REX")

   - CONFIRM      (BOOLEAN)

   - STATUSBAR    (BOOLEAN)

   - SHOWTITLE    (BOOLEAN)

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}SETSPREFS MAXENTRIES 50@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63O" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63O"
@Next "M63P"
@Prev "M63N"
@Toc "M63"

GETVPREFS
---------

@{i}Description:@{ui} Supplies the value of a single viewer  prefs  adjustment.
The  result type depends on <KeyWord>. Valid keywords are:

   - DSCREENS  (-> ViewerPrefs "Display Screens")

   - DSIZE     (-> ViewerPrefs "Display Size")

   - DITHER    (-> ViewerPrefs "Dither 8-bit Displays")

   - SUPERBM   (-> ViewerPrefs "SuperBitMap")

   - ORIGPAL   (-> ViewerPrefs "Use Original Palette")

   - DELAY     (-> ViewerPrefs "Delay")

   - VIEWERxxx (1)(-> Viewerprefs/MX Gadgets for choosing one of
     "custom screen", "external" or "window")

   - EXTCOMxxx (-> ViewerPrefs/String Gadgets for external viewers)

@{i}Result:@{ui} Depends on the keyword

   - DSCREENS  ("ASC", "REQ" oder "GLB")

   - DSIZE     ("ORIGINAL", "SMALL" oder "Tiny")

   - DITHER    (BOOLEAN)

   - SUPERBM   (BOOLEAN)

   - ORIGPAL   (BOOLEAN)

   - DELAY     (INTEGER)

   - VIEWERxxx ("CSC", "EXT" or "WIN")

   - EXTCOMxxx (STRING)

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}GETVPREFS DITHER@{ub}

---------- Footnotes ----------

(1)  xxx stands for IFF, GIF, JPG, PCX, BMP, PCD, PNM or TGA


@EndNode

@Node "M63P" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63P"
@Next "M63Q"
@Prev "M63O"
@Toc "M63"

SETVPREFS
---------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}SETVPREFS <KeyWord> <Value>@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Sets a viewer prefs adjustment to <Value> (see  also
GETVPREFS).  The argument  type  of  <Value>  depends  on the argument
<KeyWord>. Valid keywords are:

   - DSCREENS  ("ASC", "REQ" oder "GLB")

   - DSIZE     ("ORIGINAL", "SMALL" oder "Tiny")

   - DITHER    (BOOLEAN)

   - SUPERBM   (BOOLEAN)

   - ORIGPAL   (BOOLEAN)

   - DELAY     (INTEGER)

   - VIEWERxxx ("CSC", "EXT" or "WIN")

   - EXTCOMxxx (STRING)

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}SETVPREFS DSIZE SMALL@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63Q" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63Q"
@Next "M63R"
@Prev "M63P"
@Toc "M63"

GETTPREFS
---------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}GETTPREFS <KeyWord>@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Supplies the value of a single thumbnail prefs adjustment.
The  result type depends on <KeyWord>. Valid keywords are:

   - DITHER     (-> ThumbnailPrefs "Dither Thumbnail Images")

   - SHOWNAMES  (-> ThumbnailPrefs "Show File Names")

   - HIQUALITY  (-> ThumbnailPrefs "HiQuality")

   - TSIZE      (-> ThumbnailPrefs "Thumbnail Size")

@{i}Result:@{ui} Depends on the keyword

   - DITHER     ("NONE", "FLOYD" or "ORDERED")

   - SHOWNAMES  (BOOLEAN)

   - HIQUALITY  (BOOLEAN)

   - TSIZE      ("SMALL", "STD", "BIG", "HUGE" or "XLARGE")

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}GETTPREFS DITHER@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63R" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63R"
@Next "M63S"
@Prev "M63Q"
@Toc "M63"

SETTPREFS
---------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}SETTPREFS <KeyWord> <Value>@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Sets a thumbnail prefs adjustment to <Value> (see also
GETTPREFS). The argument  type  of  <Value>  depends  on the argument
<KeyWord>. Valid keywords are:

   - DITHER     ("NONE", "FLOYD" or "ORDERED")

   - SHOWNAMES  (BOOLEAN)

   - HIQUALITY  (BOOLEAN)

   - TSIZE      ("SMALL", "STD", "BIG", "HUGE" or "XLARGE")

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}SETTPREFS TSIZE STD@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63S" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63S"
@Next "M63T"
@Prev "M63R"
@Toc "M63"

GETSYSINFO
----------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}GETSYSINFO <KeyWord>@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Supplies the value of a specified system state  variable.
The  result type depends on <KeyWord>. Valid keywords are:

   - VERSION    (supplies ImageDesk's current version number)

   - GFXMODE    (tells the graphics mode e.g. "CyberGfx")

   - DESKSPACE  (tells how many thumbnails currently fits on the desk)

   - THUMBSUSED (tells how many thumbnails are currently in use)

   - CATNAME    (tells the file name of the last loaded catalog)

   - BUFENTRIES (tells the number of thumbnails in the catalog buffer)

@{i}Result:@{ui} Depends on the keyword

   - VERSION    (STRING)

   - GFXMODE    (STRING)

   - DESKSPACE  (INTEGER)

   - THUMBSUSED (INTEGER)

   - CATNAME    (STRING)

   - BUFENTRIES (INTEGER)

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}GETSYSINFO VERSION@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63T" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63T"
@Next "M63U"
@Prev "M63S"
@Toc "M63"

CLOSEBUF
--------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}CLOSEBUF@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} If a catalog buffer is active it will  be  closed  and
its  allocated memory will be freed.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}CLOSEBUF@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63U" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63U"
@Next "M63V"
@Prev "M63T"
@Toc "M63"

SAVEBUF
-------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}SAVEBUF [<FileName>]@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Saves the active catalog buffer into one single  file.  If
<FileName> has not been specified a file requester will ask for it.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}SAVEBUF "work:catalogs/gifpics.cat"@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63V" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63V"
@Next "M63W"
@Prev "M63U"
@Toc "M63"

NEXTPAGE
--------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}NEXTPAGE@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Turns to the next screen page within the catalog buffer.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}NEXTPAGE@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63W" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63W"
@Next "M63X"
@Prev "M63V"
@Toc "M63"

PREVPAGE
--------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}PREVPAGE@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Turns to the previous screen page within the catalog
buffer.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}PREVPAGE@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63X" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63X"
@Next "M63Y"
@Prev "M63W"
@Toc "M63"

SELECTRANGE
-----------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}SELECTRANGE@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Opens a special requester which enables you to select a
range  within the  catalog  buffer. All thumbnails of this range will
be then shown.  afterwards.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}SELECTRANGE@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63Y" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63Y"
@Next "M63Z"
@Prev "M63X"
@Toc "M63"

CATBROWSER
----------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}CATBROWSER [<FileName>]@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Opens the window of the Catalog Browser. See also @{i}Catalog
Browser@{ui}  in the  menu  @{i}Navigate@{ui}.  If  <FileName>  has  not  been
specified, a file requester will ask you for one.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}CATBROWSER "work:catalogs/gifpics.cat"@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63Z" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63Z"
@Next "M63_a"
@Prev "M63Y"
@Toc "M63"

RELOADCAT
---------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}RELOADCAT@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Loads the last opened catalog again.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}RELOADCAT@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63_a" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63_a"
@Next "M63_b"
@Prev "M63Z"
@Toc "M63"

REDRAW
------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}REDRAW@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Redraws the current page. Unbuffered thumbnails will be
lost!

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}REDRAW@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63_b" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63_b"
@Next "M63_c"
@Prev "M63_a"
@Toc "M63"

GETBUFPOS
---------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}GETBUFPOS <ThumbName>@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Returns the position of the thumbnail <ThumbName> within
the  catalog buffer.  This  position  for  example is required for
GETTHUMBINFO and REMFROMBUF.

@{i}Result:@{ui} Number of the position if succesful, else -1.

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}GETBUFPOS "Amiga_Pic.jpg"@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63_c" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63_c"
@Next "M63_d"
@Prev "M63_b"
@Toc "M63"

REMFROMBUF
----------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}REMFROMBUF [<Position>]@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Removes the thumbnail on position <Position> from the
catalog  buffer.  If  <Position>  is  missing, an window opens where
the user may choose the entries to remove.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}REMFROMBUF 0@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63_d" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63_d"
@Next "M63_e"
@Prev "M63_c"
@Toc "M63"

REMFROMDESK
-----------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}REMFROMDESK <Position>@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} Removes the visible thumbnail on screen position
<Position>  from  the screen. The position is required and cannot be
asked by GETBUFPOS, But the @{i}Default AREXX Script@{ui} will be supplied with
it.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}REMFROMDESK ipos@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63_e" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63_e"
@Next "M63_f"
@Prev "M63_d"
@Toc "M63"

GETTHUMBINFO
------------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}GETTHUMBINFO <Keyword1> <Position> <Keyword2>@{ub} @{i}Description:@{ui}
Supplies you with information about a  thumbnail  object  at  position
<Position>. <Keyword1> gives the thumbnail source:

   - BUF (thumbnail source  is the catalog buffer)

   - DESK (thumbnail source is the screen)

   - BROWS (thumbnail source is the browser´s buffer)

The following information may be asked (Keyword2):

   - PICTYPE   ("IFF", "GIF", "JPG", "BMP", "PCX", "TGA", "PCD" or
     "PNM")

   - PICWIDTH  (width of the corresponding picture, INTEGER)

   - PICHEIGHT (height of the corresponding picture, INTEGER)

   - PICDEPTH  (depth of the corresponding picture, INTEGER)

@{i}Result:@{ui} See above.

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}GETTHUMBINFO DESK ipos PICWIDTH@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M63_f" "ImageDeskE.guide/M63_f"
@Prev "M63_e"
@Toc "M63"

TERMINATE
---------

@{i}Syntax:@{ui} @{b}TERMINATE@{ub}

@{i}Description:@{ui} If the catalog browser is active, it will be closed. In
the other case ImageDesk   exits.  Coution,  it  is  very  problematic
to  close  an application by AREXX. So use TERMINATE very carefully.

@{i}Result:@{ui} NULL

@{i}Example:@{ui} @{b}TERMINATE@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "M7_TOOLS" "ImageDeskE.guide/M7_TOOLS"
@Next "M8_REGIS"
@Prev "M6_AREXX"
@Toc "Main"

Catalog Tools
*************

This distribution contains several  CLI-only  tools.  They  serve  for
touching  up  catalog  files  created  by ImageDesk. The templates for
running such a tool  work  in  accordance  with  the  Commodore  style
guides.  For  further  explanation  take  a  look  into  your AmigaDos
Manuals.

@{i}Remark:@{ui} With the release of ImageDesk 3.0 these tools will be partly
unnecessary because the program is now able to do some of these jobs
internally. For example, the thumbnails now will be automatically
sorted.   Removing  thumbnails  from  catalogs  is  also  possible  in
ImageDesk itself.


 @{"        CATList         " Link "M71"}    

 @{"       CATChPath        " Link "M72"}    

 @{"       CATRepack        " Link "M73"}    

 @{"        CATJoin         " Link "M74"}    

 @{"      CATRemEntry       " Link "M75"}    

 @{"        CATSort         " Link "M76"}    

 @{"       CATSplit         " Link "M77"} 


@EndNode

@Node "M71" "ImageDeskE.guide/M71"
@Next "M72"
@Toc "M7_TOOLS"

CATList
=======

Template:
---------

               @{b}CATFILE/A,P=PASSWORD/K,F=FULL/S@{ub}

Description:
------------

Lists all entries of an ImageDesk catalog file in the order  of  their
occurrence.  This  command is very useful to find out which position a
specific entry has. To remove an entry, for example, it  is  necessary
to know its position in the catalog file.

@{b}CATFILE/A@{ub}
     Path and filename of an ImageDesk catalog file.

@{b}P=PASSWORD/K@{ub}
     If a catalog file was generated by using xpk-password encryption,
     the corresponding password has to be specified here.

@{b}F=FULL/S@{ub}
     Besides position and filename, this switch directs CATList to print
     further attributes of the pictures.


@EndNode

@Node "M72" "ImageDeskE.guide/M72"
@Next "M73"
@Prev "M71"
@Toc "M7_TOOLS"

CATChPath
=========

Template:
---------

                    @{b}CATFILE/A,P=NEWPATH/A@{ub}

Description:
------------

To avoid a repeated thumbnail generation run if a  path  of  an  image
directory  has  changed,  you  should use this program. It changes the
content of the pathname in a catalog file to the choices given by  the
user.  As  only  the  header  of  a catalog file is changed, it is not
necessary to specify a password even if it has been encrypted  before.
In  opposition  to  most of the other catalog tools, CATChPath is a so
called `In Place'-operation. This means, you should better work  on  a
copy of a catalog file to avoid damaging this file if an error occurs.

@{b}CATFILE/A@{ub}
     File name of the ImageDesk catalog to work on.

@{b}P=NEWPATH@{ub}
     A string which describes the path to a image directory. It won't
     be checked for validity, so the user is responsible for it being
     correct.


@EndNode

@Node "M73" "ImageDeskE.guide/M73"
@Next "M74"
@Prev "M72"
@Toc "M7_TOOLS"

CATRepack
=========

Template:
---------

@{b}CATFILE/A,O=OUTFILE/K,X=XPKMETHOD/K,F=EFFICIENCY/N,P=PASSWORD/K@{ub}

Description:
------------

If the packing method or packing efficiency of  a  formerly  generated
catalog  file  is  to  be  changed,  this  command has to be used. For
example, you could save your catalog files uncompressed  in  ImageDesk
and  pack  them  afterwards  with  CATRepack.  For security reasons an
OUTFILE should be specified.

@{b}CATFILE/A@{ub}
     File name of the ImageDesk catalog to work on.

@{b}O=OUTFILE/K@{ub}
     Name for the resulting output file. If this argument ist missing,
     the original file will be overwritten.

@{b}X=XPKMETHOD/K@{ub}
     Packing method to be used for the catalog file. Refering to the XPK
     conventions, this has to be an uppercase, fourletter string.
     @{b}X=NUKE@{ub} for example would mean, XPK method NUKE has to be used. If
     this argument is missing or XPK has not been installed the file
     will be saved without packing.

@{b}F=EFFICIENCY/N@{ub}
     Efficiency the XPKMETHOD specified pack method should work with.
     This has to be a number in the range between 0 and 100. Default
     value is 50.

@{b}P=PASSWORD/K@{ub}
     If the catalog file has been saved key encrypted the password has
     to be specified here. This password will also be used for the new
     output file if XPKMETHOD supports passwords.


@EndNode

@Node "M74" "ImageDeskE.guide/M74"
@Next "M75"
@Prev "M73"
@Toc "M7_TOOLS"

CATJoin
=======

Template:
---------

@{b}CATFILE1/A,CATFILE2/A,AS=TO/K/A,X=XPKMETHOD/K,F=EFFICIENCY/N,P=PASSWORD/K@{ub}

Description:
------------

Joins two catalog files to a new one. Provided that you have generated
more  than one catalog file for a image directory in ImageDesk - maybe
to save memory. For later assembly this command has to be used. It  is
very  imortant  for  CATFILE1 and CATFILE2 to have the same path entry
for the image directory. CATJoin won't work if ImageDesk has not  been
registered  -  it  is the only one of the catalog tools which requires
the key file.

@{b}CATFILE1/A@{ub}
     File name of the first ImageDesk catalog file.

@{b}CATFILE2/A@{ub}
     File name of the second ImageDesk catalog file.

@{b}AS=TO/K/A@{ub}
     Name for the output file.

@{b}X=XPKMETHOD/K@{ub}
     Packing method to be used for the output file. Refering to the XPK
     conventions, this has to be an uppercase, fourletter string.  If
     this argument is missing or XPK has not been installed the file
     will be saved without packing.

@{b}F=EFFICIENCY/N@{ub}
     Efficiency the XPKMETHOD specified pack method should work with.
     This has to be a number in the range between 0 and 100. Default
     value is 50.

@{b}P=PASSWORD/K@{ub}
     If the catalog files has been password encrypted, you have to
     specify the password here. Unless the two input files use the same
     password, CATJoin returns with an error. In this case, one of them
     has to be adjusted with @{b}CATRepack@{ub} to the other one. This password
     will also be used for the output file.


@EndNode

@Node "M75" "ImageDeskE.guide/M75"
@Next "M76"
@Prev "M74"
@Toc "M7_TOOLS"

CATRemEntry
===========

Template:
---------

@{b}CATFILE/A,E=ENTRY/N/A,O=OUTFILE/K,X=XPKMETHOD/K,F=EFFICIENCY/N,P=PASSWORD/K@{ub}

Description:
------------

CATRemEntry removes the entry with the position number  ENTRY  from  a
catalog  file. This could be necessary to re-establish the consistancy
between the catalog file and the contents of the image  directory.  By
help  of  @{b}CATList@{ub}  you can find out the entry number you want to know.
The other arguments show the same behavior as they do in @{b}CATRepack@{ub}.

@{b}CATFILE/A@{ub}
     File name of the ImageDesk catalog to work on.

@{b}E=ENTRY/N/A@{ub}
     Postition of the entry to remove.

@{b}O=OUTFILE/K@{ub}
     Name for the resulting output file. If this argument is missing the
     original file will be overwritten.

@{b}X=XPKMETHOD/K@{ub}
     Packing method to be used for the output file. Refering to the XPK
     conventions, this has to be an uppercase, fourletter string.  If
     this argument is missing or XPK has not been installed the file
     will be saved without packing.

@{b}F=EFFICIENCY/N@{ub}
     Efficiency the XPKMETHOD specified pack method should work with.
     This has to be a number in the range between 0 and 100. Default
     value is 50.

@{b}P=PASSWORD/K@{ub}
     If the catalog file has been saved key encrypted the password has
     to be specified here. This password will also be used for the new
     output file if XPKMETHOD supports passwords.


@EndNode

@Node "M76" "ImageDeskE.guide/M76"
@Next "M77"
@Prev "M75"
@Toc "M7_TOOLS"

CATSort
=======

Template:
---------

@{b}CATFILE/A,O=OUTFILE/K,X=XPKMETHOD/K,F=EFFICIENCY/N,P=PASSWORD/K@{ub}

Description:
------------

Sorts the thumbnail entries of the catalog @{b}CATFILE@{ub} in  lexicographical
order of the pictures file names.

@{b}CATFILE/A@{ub}
     File name of the ImageDesk catalog to work on.

@{b}O=OUTFILE/K@{ub}
     Name for the resulting output file. If this argument is missing the
     original file will be overwritten.

@{b}X=XPKMETHOD/K@{ub}
     Packing method to be used for the output file. Refering to the XPK
     conventions, this has to be an uppercase, fourletter string.  If
     this argument is missing or XPK has not been installed the file
     will be saved without packing.

@{b}F=EFFICIENCY/N@{ub}
     Efficiency the XPKMETHOD specified pack method should work with.
     This has to be a number in the range between 0 and 100. Default
     value is 50.

@{b}P=PASSWORD/K@{ub}
     If the catalog file has been saved key encrypted the password has
     to be specified here. This password will also be used for the new
     output file if XPKMETHOD supports passwords.


@EndNode

@Node "M77" "ImageDeskE.guide/M77"
@Prev "M76"
@Toc "M7_TOOLS"

CATSplit
========

Template:
---------

@{b}CATFILE/A,E=MAXENTRIES/N/A,O=OUTFILE/K,X=XPKMETHOD/K,F=EFFICIENCY/N,P=PASSWORD/K@{ub}

Description:
------------

Splits the input catalog @{b}CATFILE@{ub} into several  smaller  catalogs.  The
resulting catalogs will have @{b}MAXENTRIES@{ub} at most.

@{b}CATFILE/A@{ub}
     File name of the ImageDesk catalog to work on.

@{b}E=MAXENTRIES/N/A@{ub}
     Number of thumbnails a resulting catalog should contain at the
     most.

@{b}O=OUTFILE/K@{ub}
     Name for the resulting output file. If this argument is missing the
     original file will be overwritten.

@{b}X=XPKMETHOD/K@{ub}
     Packing method to be used for the output file. Refering to the XPK
     conventions, this has to be an uppercase, fourletter string.  If
     this argument is missing or XPK has not been installed the file
     will be saved without packing.

@{b}F=EFFICIENCY/N@{ub}
     Efficiency the XPKMETHOD specified pack method should work with.
     This has to be a number in the range between 0 and 100. Default
     value is 50.

@{b}P=PASSWORD/K@{ub}
     If the catalog file has been saved key encrypted the password has
     to be specified here. This password will also be used for the new
     output file if XPKMETHOD supports passwords.


@EndNode

@Node "M8_REGIS" "ImageDeskE.guide/M8_REGIS"
@Next "M9_UPDAT"
@Prev "M7_TOOLS"
@Toc "Main"

As you may have noticed, ImageDesk is a shareware product. Nearly  all
functions  are  available for testing without paying any money. If you
think ImageDesk is worth the amount of 30 DM or $20,-, refer to me for
your  personal key file. If you want me to ship ImageDesk via airmail,
you have to include an additional $10 (the airmail postage is 16 DM!).
Please notice, airmail shipping makes no sense if you live in europe.

The key file  method  offers  the  advantage  of  enjoying  the  whole
functionality  of  new ImageDesk releases immediately. You do not have
to wait until I send you a new fully featured version.

Besides the key file, you'll get the latest release of  the  ImageDesk
distribution and a printed manual.

To get registered for ImageDesk, please print the  file  @{b}OrderForm@{ub}  on
your  printer  (if no printer is available, write off this text), fill
up this form and send it to the given address. I will endeavor to  act
upon  your registration within two weeks after I get the register form
and the  shareware  fee.  In  most  cases  it  will  be  done  faster.
Prospectively the key files will be shipped by (snail)mail.

The author reserves the right, to not accept register requests.


@EndNode

@Node "M9_UPDAT" "ImageDeskE.guide/M9_UPDAT"
@Next "MA_RIGHT"
@Prev "M8_REGIS"
@Toc "Main"

Updates
*******

When you become a registered user, you will get the latest release  of
ImageDesk  together  with  your  personal  key  file. Thereby, you are
independent from direct support by the author. You'll get  the  latest
releases from Aminet (eventually other PD archives, too) instead.

If you do not have the possibility to get ImageDesk this way  you  can
get  it  directly  from the author. In this case, send me a letter and
include 5 DM or $5 if you do not live within the  EU.  This  offer  is
available to registered users only.


@EndNode

@Node "MA_RIGHT" "ImageDeskE.guide/MA_RIGHT"
