@Node "MB_HISTO" "ImageDeskE.guide/MB_HISTO"
@Next "MC_THANX"
@Prev "MA_RIGHT"
@Toc "Main"

0.97 Beta
---------

First beta release.

0.98 Beta
---------

   @{b}*@{ub} Now the default public screen is left to the workbench as long as
     it is not necessary for ImageDesk to declare its screen to the
     default publicscreen.

   @{b}*@{ub} Before closing the screen, ImageDesk now checks if other
     applications have opened their windows on ImageDesk's publicscreen.

   @{b}*@{ub} Don't try to load IFF-ILBM images with unknown compression types
     anymore.

   @{b}*@{ub} File names for the external viewers may contain spaces.

   @{b}*@{ub} The slidergadgets in the @{b}Load Catalog@{ub} control window are now
     managed correctly.

   @{b}*@{ub} A few catalog file tools have been added (@{b}CATList@{ub}, @{b}CATChPath@{ub},
     @{b}CATRepack@{ub}, @{b}CATJoin@{ub} and @{b}CATRemEntry@{ub}).

1.0 - first public release
--------------------------

   @{b}*@{ub} Added internal window viewer.

   @{b}*@{ub} Removed small bug in the BMP reader.

   @{b}*@{ub} System font will be opened correctly now.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added dither option for 8-bit displays.

1.01
----

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed bug: Village Screenmode requester sometimes has been opened
     on the workbench screen.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed bug in the JPEG Picasso viewer: 8-bit JPEGs were displayed
     incorrectly on the 8-bit screens.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed a wrong palette entry in the 8-bit Picasso viewer.

   @{b}*@{ub} Improved display speed of the window viewer for truecolor images.

1.02
----

   @{b}*@{ub} Added Scrollbars to the window viewer.

1.1
---

   @{b}*@{ub} Added Switch `Use Original Palette' for the window viewers.

   @{b}*@{ub} Now supports and generates project icons for catalogs.

1.11
----

   @{b}*@{ub} Thumbnail generation from 4-bit BMPs reported an error - Fixed.

   @{b}*@{ub} Now The name of the screen is displayed instead of the ID in the
     System Prefs window.

1.12
----

   @{b}*@{ub} 'Default Public Screen' has not been set back to workbench if the
     Picasso screenrequester has been used - Fixed.

1.2
---

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed bug: If no complete path was specified for a catalog file to
     be generated, some problems could have been arised while saving.

   @{b}*@{ub} CyberGraphics and standard 8 bit intuition screens are supported.

   @{b}*@{ub} The state of @{i}Show Image Infos@{ui} is stored in the prefs file.

   @{b}*@{ub} The information window now shows the current graphics board mode.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added new menu item @{i}Ask Before Cleaning Desk@{ui}.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Open Catalog@{ui} now branches into subitems: @{i}Selectable@{ui} and @{i}Quick@{ui}.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added new menu item @{i}Mark & Delete@{ui} for multiple thumbnail removal.

   @{b}*@{ub} Changed (Improved?) most of the screen displaying routines.

   @{b}*@{ub} The image information window now shows the path of the file too.

1.21
----

   @{b}*@{ub} The number of entries per catalog is now selectable in the range
     of 3 and 600.

   @{b}*@{ub} It is now possible to interrupt the internal viewers at any time.

   @{b}*@{ub} A few internal changes.

1.22
----

   @{b}*@{ub} Removed problems in conjunction with MFR.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed bug in the window viewers which caused a very high CPU-load
     factor.

   @{b}*@{ub} Compacted program code in the Picasso screen viewers.

1.23
----

   @{b}*@{ub} IFF DCOL (Direct COLor) chunks are supported now.

1.3
---

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed bug: The ILBM decoder had problems reading truecolor images
     which contained additional palette information.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed problem of reading ILBMs containing ANNO Chunks with a wrong
     Chunk length field.

   @{b}*@{ub} Now it is possible to have file names being rendered below the
     thumbnail images.

1.4
---

   @{b}*@{ub} Added @{i}Thumbnail Prefs@{ui} window.

   @{b}*@{ub} Now supports further thumbnail sizes.

   @{b}*@{ub} Uses own font for thumbnail text.

   @{b}*@{ub} New option: @{i}Print Execution Command@{ui}.

   @{b}*@{ub} Prefs windows retouched.

   @{b}*@{ub} Changed prefs file structure.

   @{b}*@{ub} New catalog file structure.

   @{b}*@{ub} Adapted all @{i}Catalog Tools@{ui} to the new structure.

1.41
----

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed size and alignment problems on temporary rastports.

1.42
----

   @{b}*@{ub} Support for environment variable @{i}KEYPATH@{ui} added which specifies the
     location of the key file.

1.5
---

   @{b}*@{ub} Integrated AREXX Port.

   @{b}*@{ub} Increased GIF decoding speed (twice as fast).

   @{b}*@{ub} ImageDescriptor instead of ScreenDescriptor is used for size
     determination of GIF thumbnails now.

   @{b}*@{ub} Removed several smaller bugs.

1.6
---

   @{b}*@{ub} Now executes AREXX programs on thumbnail click.

   @{b}*@{ub} Enhanced hotkey handling.

   @{b}*@{ub} New option @{b}HiQuality@{ub}.

   @{b}*@{ub} Further AREXX commands.

   @{b}*@{ub} Enhanced slider gadget handling.

   @{b}*@{ub} File requester attributes are stored in the prefs now.

   @{b}*@{ub} Larger thumbnail sizes possible.

   @{b}*@{ub} Config will be saved before ImageDesk exits.

   @{b}*@{ub} Bug in the PCX reader removed.

   @{b}*@{ub} Reduced stack consumption.

2.0
---

   @{b}*@{ub} New structured menu.

   @{b}*@{ub} Catalogs are held in memory.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fast, screenwise turn over within the catalog buffer.

   @{b}*@{ub} Introduction of the @{i}Catalog Browsers@{ui}.

   @{b}*@{ub} Significant speed improvement when figuring the thumbnail images.

   @{b}*@{ub} New option for dithering @{i}Floyd Steinberg@{ui}.

   @{b}*@{ub} Full tooltype support for Project-Icons.

   @{b}*@{ub} Takes care of IFFs aspect ratio.

   @{b}*@{ub} Optionally writes an error report.

   @{b}*@{ub} Introduction of new Catalog Tools @{b}CATSort@{ub} and @{b}CATSplit@{ub}.

   @{b}*@{ub} New AREXX commands.

   @{b}*@{ub} Removed several bugs.

2.1
---

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{i}Default AREXX Script@{ui} will now be supplied with 3 parameters.

   @{b}*@{ub} AREXX Commands @{b}GETSPREFS@{ub}, @{b}SETSPREFS@{ub}, @{b}GETSYSINFO@{ub} and @{b}OPENCAT@{ub}
     extended.

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{i}Catalog Browser@{ui} now allows to start AREXX scripts.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed bug in @{i}Mark & Delete@{ui}.

   @{b}*@{ub} Increased the size of some internal string buffers.

   @{b}*@{ub} Introduction of the ImageDesk tool @{b}MIPFIC@{ub}.

   @{b}*@{ub} New option in ViewerPrefs to disable SuperBitmaps for the Window
     viewer.

   @{b}*@{ub} Appertaining new keyword @{b}SUPERBM@{ub} for the AREXX commands GETVPREFS
     and SETVPREFS.

   @{b}*@{ub} Totaly rewritten bufferd image readers for better stability.

3.0
---

   @{b}*@{ub} Datatypes support.

   @{b}*@{ub} Dynamic thumbnail handling and automatic buffer sorting.

   @{b}*@{ub} Enables automatically catalog updates

   @{b}*@{ub} Now allows to remove single thumbnails from a catalog.

   @{b}*@{ub} Some screen layout changes.

   @{b}*@{ub} Now it is possible to hide or to show the screen title and a
     status bar.

   @{b}*@{ub} Some new AREXX commands.

   @{b}*@{ub} Many internal changes and enhancements.

3.04
----

   @{b}*@{ub} Allows up to 50 XPK packers.

   @{b}*@{ub} No longer crashes when scanning executables.

   @{b}*@{ub} Accepts some of former ignored GIFs

   @{b}*@{ub} Shortcut <Amiga>+<R> now works.

   @{b}*@{ub} Starts user definable AREXX scripts by pressing F1 to F10.

   @{b}*@{ub} The window viewers no longer have problems with 8-Bit JPEGs.

   @{b}*@{ub} Now includes an italian 3.0 guide file.


@EndNode

